  <h3>Specialized Grammar Tools</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Conjuguemos:</strong> Interactive verb conjugation practice with games</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Portuguese:</strong> European Portuguese focus with grammar explanations</li>
    <li><strong>Portuguese with Leo:</strong> Brazilian Portuguese grammar lessons</li>
    <li><strong>Cambridge Dictionary:</strong> Comprehensive Portuguese-English dictionary</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Pronunciation Resources</h2>

  <h3>Nasal Vowel Mastery</h3>

  <p>Nasal vowels represent one of the most challenging aspects of Portuguese pronunciation. These resources can help:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Forvo:</strong> Native speaker pronunciations for thousands of Portuguese words</li>
    <li><strong>Speechling:</strong> Speech recognition feedback on your pronunciation</li>
    <li><strong>FluentForever:</strong> Minimal pair training for phonemic distinctions</li>
    <li><strong>YouTube channels:</strong> Numerous Portuguese teachers offer pronunciation tutorials</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Phonetic Transcription Tools</h3>

  <p>The International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA) helps understand Portuguese sounds:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Sound</th>
        <th>IPA</th>
        <th>Example</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Nasal 'a'</td>
        <td>/ɐ̃/</td>
        <td>"irmã" (sister)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Open 'e'</td>
        <td>/ɛ/</td>
        <td>"pés" (feet)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Closed 'o'</td>
        <td>/o/</td>
        <td>"botas" (boots)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Palatal 'lh'</td>
        <td>/ʎ/</td>
        <td>"filho" (son)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

